{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 20:40:45.821807", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting diagnosis report — Clos / EBGP lab\\n\\nSummary\\n- The control plane (EBGP) appears to be converged and routes for all pod /24 host networks are present across routers.\\n- One clear data-plane anomaly was found: a static blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/30 exists on leaf_router_0_0 and is the more-specific match that overrides the connected 10.0.0.0/24. This causes traffic for the 10.0.0.0 network on that box to be dropped.\\n- Impact: host pc_0_0 (10.0.0.x) shows reachability problems; other hosts (including pc_0_1) are able to reach remote prefixes.\\n\\nEvidence (extracted from gathered data)\\n1) Host reachability test (get_reachability)\\n- pc_0_0 -> pc_3_0 (10.3.0.2): status = unknown\\n- pc_0_0 -> pc_2_2 (10.2.2.2): status = unknown\\n- Example of a working host for comparison:\\n  - pc_0_1 -> pc_3_0 (10.3.0.2): tx=2 rx=2 loss_percent=0.0 rtt_avg_ms=2.196 (status ok)\\n\\n2) Route table on leaf_router_0_0 (show ip route)\\n- Relevant lines showing the anomaly:\\n  - C>* 10.0.0.0/24 is directly connected, eth8, ...\\n  - S>* 10.0.0.0/30 [1/0] unreachable (blackhole), weight 1, ...\\n  (the /30 static blackhole is present and marked in the RIB; because /30 is more specific than /24 it will be chosen for matching traffic to 10.0.0.0 addresses)\\n\\n3) BGP tables (sample)\\n- leaf_router_0_0 advertises and sees 10.0.0.0/24 as local (BGP table shows 10.0.0.0/24 with next-hop 0.0.0.0).\\n- Other routers (spines, super-spine) have routes for the 10.0.x.0/24 networks and the global EBGP topology looks populated (no wide-scale missing BGP prefixes).\\n\\nLocalization — faulty/implicated device(s)\\n- leaf_router_0_0: contains a static blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/30 (S>* 10.0.0.0/30 unreachable (blackhole) ...). This is the single configuration item shown that directly explains the data-plane failure experienced by pc_0_0.\\n- No evidence in collected outputs of BGP session flap or missing advertisements on other routers; BGP tables and routes on spine/super-spine routers look normal.\\n\\nRoot cause analysis\\n- Root cause (most likely): A static route installed on leaf_router_0_0 that points 10.0.0.0/30 to a blackhole. Because route selection uses longest-prefix match, the /30 blackhole is preferred over the connected /24, causing the router to drop packets destined for the 10.0.0.0 network rather than forwarding them.\\n- Symptom mapping:\\n  - Host pc_0_0 (in 10.0.0.0/24) cannot reach other subnets (unknown ping results). This is consistent with leaf_router_0_0 discarding traffic due to the blackhole prefix taking precedence.\\n  - Other hosts (e.g., pc_0_1) can reach remote prefixes because their leaf router does not have the blackhole more-specific prefix and normal forwarding/BGP resolution works.\\n\\nOther observations\\n- EBGP connectivity and route propagation appear healthy: BGP tables on leaves/spines/super-spine show learned /24 prefixes across the fabric.\\n- No other obvious misconfigurations (AS mismatches, missing next-hops, or withdrawn prefixes) were detected in the provided BGP dumps.\\n- The presence of a /30 blackhole is anomalous in this topology (inter-router links were expected to use /31; host subnets are /24). That suggests the static blackhole likely resulted from an operator/configuration mistake or an automated process that injected a wrong aggregate/static route.\\n\\nImpact summary\\n- Localized outage for the 10.0.0.0/24 host(s) serviced by leaf_router_0_0 (pc_0_0): traffic destined off-link is being blackholed at that leaf.\\n- The rest of the data center fabric and BGP route distribution remain functional.\\n\\nData sources used\\n- get_reachability results (host ping status)\\n- frr_show_ip_route outputs for leaf_router_0_0 (route table lines quoted above) and other routers\\n- frr_get_bgp_conf / BGP tables (which show prefix presence and that BGP is converged)\\n\\nNo remediation actions were performed (per instructions). If you want, I can next:\\n- show the exact static route configuration line(s) on leaf_router_0_0 (e.g., show running-config) to confirm source of blackhole,\\n- or gather any system logs or timestamps related to when that static/blackhole route was added., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='3d94b724-2fcd-48cf-b007-bca4bf159a5c'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5-mini", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
