{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 20:41:02.302712", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Thanks — I reviewed the diagnosis and submitted the solution.\n\nSummary of submission\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty device: leaf_router_0_0\n- root cause selected: host_static_blackhole\n\nRecommended immediate remediation (suggested next steps)\n1. On leaf_router_0_0, remove the erroneous static blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/30 (the config line that created \"S>* 10.0.0.0/30 unreachable (blackhole) ...\").\n   - Example FRR commands (verify before applying):\n     - configure terminal\n     - no ip route 10.0.0.0/30 blackhole\n     - write memory\n2. Verify route table after removal:\n   - show ip route 10.0.0.0\n   - Confirm C>* 10.0.0.0/24 is selected and no /30 entry exists.\n3. Re-test host reachability from pc_0_0 to remote hosts (pc_3_0, pc_2_2).\n4. Optionally, check running-config and audit logs to determine how the static blackhole was introduced (operator error, automation bug) and apply fixes to prevent recurrence (config validation, change control).\n5. If you want, I can fetch the exact static route lines from leaf_router_0_0 running-config or pull logs/timestamps to help with root-cause for change control.\n\nIf you want me to perform any of the verification/remediation commands or gather the running-config/logs, tell me which and I'll run them.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1866, "output_tokens": 330, "total_tokens": 2196, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 0}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
